<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="156" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/746.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires
                                        at London</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 31, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Foreign Office intend to reply to Japan that although the British
                                Government can not undertake absolutely to prevent their nationals
                                from making loans in future, the Government are ready to “use their
                                influence as far as possible to prevent” such financial
                                assistance.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>